Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"PolarizedDensityOperator", "::", "usage"}], "=", 
   "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
   "\"\<PolarizedDensityOperator[<args>] sets up a density operator in which \
one, or several spins, are polarized along an arbitrary axis. In general the \
polarization levels and polarization directions may be defined individually \
for each spin. \nOne special case of the syntax is \
PolarizedDensityOperator[{p,\\\"z\\\"}] which generates a density operator \
with polarization level p along the z-axis for all spins in the current \
SpinSystem[]. Similarly, PolarizedDensityOperator[{j,k,l},{p,\\\"z\\\"}] \
generates a density operator with polarization level p along the z-axis for \
spins {j,k,l}. \nThe most general syntax is \
PolarizedDensityOperator[{{j,{polj,axisj}},{k,{polk,axisk}}..},spinsystem] \
which constructs a density operator for spinsystem, corresponding to \
polarization polj for spins j along the axis axisj, and similarly for spins \
k, etc. The polarizations {polj,polk..} are in the range -1 to +1, with -1 \
indicating complete negative polarization, and +1 indicating complete \
positive polarization. If a polarization argument is omitted, a value of +1 \
is assumed.\nIf spinsystem is omitted, the current SpinSystem[] is assumed. \n\
The spin labels {j,k..} must be members of spinsystem and cannot be \
duplicated.\nThe axis arguments may take values \\\"x\\\",\\\"y\\\", \
\\\"z\\\", or a number \[Phi], or a pair of polar angles {\[Theta],\[Phi]}. \
The phase \[Phi] denotes an axis in the transverse plane. The polar angles {\
\[Theta],\[Phi]} may be used to define an arbitrary direction. If an axis \
argument is omitted, the axis \\\"z\\\" is assumed. \nThe syntax \
PolarizedDensityOperator[{j,k..},{pol,axis},spinsystem] assumes all spins \
{j,k..} have polarization level pol along axis. \nThe syntax \
PolarizedDensityOperator[{j,k..},pol,spinsystem] assumes all spins {j,k..} \
have polarization level pol along the z-axis.\nThe syntax \
PolarizedDensityOperator[pol, spinsystem] assumes all spins in the spinsystem \
have polarization level pol along the z-axis.\nThe syntax \
PolarizedDensityOperator[axis, spinsystem] assumes all spins in the \
spinsystem have polarization level +1 along axis.\n\>\""}], ";"}]], "Input",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.674295775465962*^9, 3.6742961345247307`*^9}, {
   3.674296173261022*^9, 3.674296434151524*^9}, {3.6746242940319858`*^9, 
   3.674624387087596*^9}, {3.674624473246602*^9, 3.6746245511553926`*^9}, {
   3.674624626664239*^9, 3.674624800150639*^9}, {3.674624902025001*^9, 
   3.674624914318118*^9}, {3.681035834717311*^9, 3.6810359896943083`*^9}, {
   3.681036056308502*^9, 3.681036085605449*^9}, {3.681036160126233*^9, 
   3.681036164139742*^9}, 3.681036195180877*^9, {3.6810373461815166`*^9, 
   3.681037363602559*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0ba12b21-bc4e-4c67-87c1-\
92d3b2b9e94a"]
}, Closed]],

