  3.674025069204586*^9}, {3.674025951694894*^9, 3.674025968860887*^9}, {
  3.674026112925443*^9, 3.6740261156127987`*^9}, {3.674560054006096*^9, 
  3.674560055636259*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"174ec6c0-1427-4428-b5d9-\
fafe78286f57"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["explanation", "Subsubsection",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.674559277367179*^9, 3.674559284971189*^9}, {
  3.674626533368417*^9, 
  3.674626535007709*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3833c206-4fdc-45d2-b2df-\
86b42c29b678"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "When several spins are polarized, the density operator is constructed from \
the Dot product of the polarized density operators of the individual spins. \
However a normalization factor is required to ensure that the trace of the \
product is still 1. Since each individual operator contains a term \
dim\[Times]1 + (traceless operators), where dim is the dimension of Hilbert \
space [see below], the Dot product must be multiplied by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["dim", 
    RowBox[{"n", "-", "1"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f4c7d50d-7adf-432c-ab3b-35400ff4404e"],
 "where n is the number of polarized spin terms, in order to ensure that the \
final operator also has the form dim\[Times]1 + (traceless operators), and \
has trace unity. "
}], "Text",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.674560113786664*^9, 3.674560122595558*^9}, {
  3.674626538303726*^9, 3.674626724189169*^9}, {3.674626837198799*^9, 
  3.674626838741664*^9}, {3.674626995526567*^9, 
  3.674626999187199*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"031796db-78ea-4600-a37b-\
88c33631b75f"]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["code", "Subsubsection",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.674559277367179*^9, 
  3.674559284971189*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a0c28bbc-db20-4bdc-a91a-\
0ca0395d1e86"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"PolarizedDensityOperator", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"polspecs", ":", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"{", 
         RowBox[{"_", ",", 
          RowBox[{"{", 
           RowBox[{"_", ",", "_"}], "}"}]}], "}"}], ".."}], "}"}]}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"spinsys_", "?", "MatrixQ"}]}], "]"}], ":=", 
   "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"If", "[", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"FreeQ", "[", 
        RowBox[{"#", ",", "$Failed"}], "]"}], ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
       RowBox[{"(*", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"PolarizedDensityOperator", "[", 
          RowBox[{"polspecs", ",", "spinsys"}], "]"}], "="}], "*)"}], 
       RowBox[{"Simplify", "@", 
        RowBox[{"Expand", "[", "#", "]"}]}], ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
       "$Failed"}], "]"}], "&"}], "@", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{"Module", "[", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"{", "dim", "}"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"(", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"dim", "=", 
         RowBox[{"BasisDimension", "[", 
          RowBox[{"ZeemanBasis", "[", "spinsys", "]"}], "]"}]}], ";", 
        "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"dim", "^", 
          RowBox[{"(", 
           RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"Length", "[", "polspecs", "]"}], "-", "1"}], ")"}]}], 
         "\[Times]", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
         RowBox[{"Apply", "[", 
          RowBox[{"Dot", ",", 
           RowBox[{
            RowBox[{
             RowBox[{"SingleSpinPolarizedDensityOperator", "[", 
              RowBox[{"#", ",", "spinsys"}], "]"}], "&"}], "/@", 
            "polspecs"}]}], "]"}]}]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", ")"}]}], 
     "]"}]}]}], ";"}]], "Input",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.674469647990242*^9, 3.674469697692625*^9}, {
   3.674471762879155*^9, 3.674471860212021*^9}, {3.6746249684738398`*^9, 
   3.6746249948000298`*^9}, {3.674626741174267*^9, 3.6746268134710417`*^9}, {
   3.6810371938353176`*^9, 3.681037196477283*^9}, {3.681112133257579*^9, 
   3.681112136450428*^9}, 3.68111255873873*^9, {3.8969508522186775`*^9, 
   3.896950856044549*^9}, {3.896950984773972*^9, 
   3.8969509849201746`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"7e493c91-c162-4624-bc52-\
eff1b090eb60"]
}, Closed]]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["single spin", "Subsection",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.66732859726386*^9, 3.667328616232379*^9}, {
  3.6740248144387293`*^9, 3.674024816388267*^9}, {3.674025062534934*^9, 
  3.674025069204586*^9}, {3.674025951694894*^9, 3.674025968860887*^9}, {
  3.674026112925443*^9, 3.6740261156127987`*^9}, {3.674560054006096*^9, 
  3.674560069316039*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b4f0dc51-cf98-47bd-b8e9-\
7f93c5899935"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["explanation", "Subsubsection",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.674559277367179*^9, 3.674559288278892*^9}, {
  3.6745609265418777`*^9, 
  3.6745609283510118`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c1e568cb-0226-42d6-82c8-\
a70408211edd"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "First consider a single spin, in a spinsystem consisting of that spin \
alone. \nAssume that the density operator for a single spin polarized with \
level p along the z-axis is given by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["\[Rho]", "p"], "=", " ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"a", " ", "1"}], " ", "+", " ", 
     RowBox[{"b", " ", "p", " ", 
      SubscriptBox["I", "z"]}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "2a49671c-bd8b-434c-803c-fb6e0d46211e"],
 ", and determining a and b. Since the trace of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Rho]", "p"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "114eb57b-7ec2-4d77-b9fa-6318abdba5de"],
 " must be 1 (sum of populations) then a = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"2", "I"}], "+", "1"}], ")"}], 
    RowBox[{"-", "1"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "feab5c69-6094-4b3a-97d0-780fdc5b3361"],
 ". For b we can demand that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"<", 
      SubscriptBox["M", "max"]}], "|", 
     SubscriptBox["\[Rho]", "p"], "|", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["M", "max"], ">"}]}], " ", "=", "1"}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"c7f1b68d-463f-455a-89a7-ce8d3d3207b9"],
 " in the case p=1. This leads to ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"<", 
     SubscriptBox["M", "max"]}], "|", 
    SubscriptBox["\[Rho]", "p"], "|", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["M", "max"], ">"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b1cbffdc-5ec3-4da4-bd39-ded639f2aaa3"],
 " = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"<", "I"}], "|", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"a", " ", "1"}], " ", "+", " ", 
      RowBox[{"b", "  ", 
       SubscriptBox["I", "z"]}]}], "|", 
     RowBox[{"I", ">"}]}], " ", "=", " ", "1.", " "}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"3d9d549b-27b1-41a0-910f-aed77bbd578b"],
 "\nThis gives a + Ib =1 and hence b=(1-a)/I. \nSince a = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"2", "I"}], "+", "1"}], ")"}], 
    RowBox[{"-", "1"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "dc2b8ff4-1c9c-45ca-ab42-a1a3f82e0d33"],
 ", \nb = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{"1", "-", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"2", "I"}], "+", "1"}], ")"}], 
      RowBox[{"-", "1"}]]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "8445719e-930c-46a7-964f-3b081a484d90"],
 ")/I = ((2I+1)-1)/I(2I+1) = 2/(2I+1).\nHence ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["\[Rho]", "p"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox[
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"2", "I"}], "+", "1"}], ")"}], 
      RowBox[{"-", "1"}]], 
     RowBox[{"(", " ", 
      RowBox[{"1", " ", "+", " ", 
       RowBox[{"2", " ", "p", " ", 
        SubscriptBox["I", "z"]}]}], ")"}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"76f8c7f8-e589-476b-9480-3da9e1dd6cbc"],
 " for a single spin in a single-spin system.\nWhen this spin is embedded in \
a larger system so that the total Hilbert space has dimension dim, then the \
unit trace of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Rho]", "p"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "21581e6d-8bc1-40f0-841f-07f06a0e40c2"],
 "is ensured by dividing this operator by (dim/(2I+1)) which is the dimension \
of the Hilbert subspace excluding the single spin. Hence the general \
expression for ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Rho]", "p"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d79a3160-c457-40b4-82dc-c9c2f6f2731c"],
 " , for a single polarized spin in a multiple-spin system, is\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["\[Rho]", "p"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox["dim", 
      RowBox[{"-", "1"}]], "(", " ", 
     RowBox[{"1", " ", "+", " ", 
      RowBox[{"2", " ", "p", " ", 
       SubscriptBox["I", "z"]}]}], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "8e71ef85-7408-447d-bfb1-820ec9f71084"]
}], "Text",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.674560960886558*^9, 3.67456151172588*^9}, {
   3.674561574490003*^9, 3.674561579822866*^9}, {3.674626124409196*^9, 
   3.6746262647397823`*^9}, 3.674626353060953*^9, {3.674626420424447*^9, 
   3.674626430669603*^9}, {3.67462702505212*^9, 
   3.674627053884711*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9655a941-440d-4bb6-8f62-\
fe63ec1ac817"]
}, Closed]],

